	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />At least in the US, it is held that bitmap fonts are not protected by copyright or patent. They could be protected under trademark or servicemark, but then only when with specific text. (Pure vector fonts are also not, but the kerning program inside the font is copyrighted). I do not know the status of bitmap fonts in europe, but vector fonts are covered there.
<br />
<br />Also, we just discuessed this in another post- <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=93802#93802">http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopi ... 3802#93802</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />Note that fonts with single-pixel-wide strokes may have unacceptable color fringing on the NES's NTSC output.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


