	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I believe slobu was referring to the areas outside $20-$7F, which can contain building blocks useful for making art. It's called <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Text_semigraphics" class="postlink">text semigraphics</a>, and it consists of extensions to ASCII art. I can think of "PETSCII art" (on the Commodore 64), so-called "ANSI art" (really IBM code page 437), "Shift JIS art" (incorporating Chinese characters, Japanese characters, and various geometric characters), and "Unicode art" (using box drawing, block elements, and likewise inherited from CP437 and other old standards).
<br />
<br />As for single-wide strokes, I don't see a problem with them in <a href="http://pineight.com/mw/index.php?title=File:Action_53_menu_on_SDTV.jpg" class="postlink">one of my projects</a>, at least when only grays are involved ($0F $00 $10 $20).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
