	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Also, <a href="http://kofler.dot.at/c64/font_01.html" class="postlink">here</a> are a large number of C64 charsets, with varying amounts of character coverage. There are 8x8, 8x16, 16x8, and even a few 16x16 sets included. They're not directly usable on the NES as they're in GIF as well as zipped raw C64 binary (1bpp) so you'll have to re-pixel (or convert from raw binary to NES pattern format) any that you may want to use. Some of the sets also include graphic characters.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


